{
  "texts": [
    "Activist investors and ESG funds use these insights to prioritize shareholder engagement, proxy voting strategies, and capital reallocation to higher-scoring firms [32].Behavioral finance research indicates that investors reward transparency and accountability.",
    "Firms with AI-validated disclosures tend to see lower bid-ask spreads, improved analyst coverage, and greater access to green bonds or ESGlinked debt instruments.",
    "Figure 4 demonstrates the correlation between AI-driven ESG reporting and elevated investor confidence levels.Moreover, investor preference is shifting toward dynamic ESG reporting, where AI enables quarterly or even monthly updates rather than static annual statements.",
    "This responsiveness is especially valuable in sectors with rapid ESG exposure changes-like technology, extractives, or consumer goods.In sum, AI-validated ESG signals enhance market confidence, reduce information asymmetry, and foster a culture of continuous accountability.",
    "Investors are not only demanding better ESG data but also rewarding firms that use advanced technologies to deliver it."
  ]
}